trans-unit.source: The DsmlResponseDocument class is a read-only collection generated as a response to a <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlRequestDocument"></xref> object that contains zero, or more, objects derived from <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse"></xref>.
The CopyTo method copies the entire collection to a one-dimensional array, starting at the specified index of the target array.
A one-dimensional array that is the destination of the elements copied from the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlRequestDocument"></xref> object.
The zero-based index of `value` where copying begins.
value is a null reference ( in Visual Basic).
i is less than zero.
value is multidimensional -or- The number of elements in the source is greater than the available space from *i* to the end of the destination value.
The type of the source cannot be cast automatically to the type of the destination value.
The Count property contains the number of <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse"></xref> objects in this collection.
The number of <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse"></xref> objects in this collection.
The GetEnumerator method returns an enumerator for the entire <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument"></xref> collection.
An <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator> object for the entire collection.
The IsErrorResponse property specifies whether an error response has occurred.
This property is <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if an error response has occurred; <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>, otherwise.
The IsOperationError property specifies whether an operation error response has occurred.
This property is <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if an operation error has occurred; <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>, otherwise.
The IsSynchronized property contains a value that indicates whether access to the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument"></xref> is synchronized (thread-safe).

<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if access to the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument"></xref> is synchronized (thread-safe); otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
The Item property contains the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse"></xref> object at the specified index.
The zero-based index value at which the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse"></xref> object is found.
The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse"></xref> object at the specified index.
The RequestId property contains the RequestID associated with the document.
This property is read-only and throws an exception if you attempt to set the property value.
The RequestID associated with the document.
You attempted to set the property value.
The SyncRoot property contains an object that can be used to synchronize access to the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument"></xref>.
Derived classes can provide synchronized versions of the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument> using the SyncRoot property.

The synchronizing code must perform operations on the SyncRoot of the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument>, not directly on the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument>.
This ensures proper operation of collections derived from other objects.
Specifically, it maintains proper synchronization with other threads that might be simultaneously modifying the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument> object.
An object that can be used to synchronize access to the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument"></xref>.

The <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument.System.Collections.ICollection.CopyTo*> method copies the entire <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument"></xref> collection to a one-dimensional array, starting at the specified index of the target array.
A one-dimensional array that is the destination of the elements copied from the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument"></xref> object.
The zero-based index of `value` where copying begins.

The <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument.System.Collections.ICollection.Count*> property gets the number of <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse"></xref> objects in this collection.
The number of <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse"></xref> objects.

The <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument.System.Collections.ICollection.IsSynchronized*> property gets a value that indicates whether access to the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument"></xref> is synchronized (thread-safe).

<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if access to the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument"></xref> is synchronized (thread-safe); otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.

The <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument.System.Collections.ICollection.SyncRoot*> property gets an object that can be used to synchronize access to the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument"></xref>.
An object that can be used to synchronize access to <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument"></xref>.
The ToXml method transforms each <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse"></xref> object in the collection into an <xref href="System.Xml.XmlDocument"></xref> object.
The transformed <xref href="System.Xml.XmlDocument"></xref> object.
